[00:07.50]I ran with the crowd, I wore the mask
[00:10.87]Chasing every trend, every moment that wouldn’t last
[00:14.24]Ink on my skin, approval in my eyes
[00:17.61]If they said I was winning, I thought I was alive
[00:20.99]Mirrors meant more than my soul inside
[00:24.36]If it looked good on the outside, I was fine
[00:27.73]But the louder the cheers, the quieter my heart
[00:31.11]Every new thing just tore me apart
[00:34.48]Then You found me right where I stood
[00:37.85]When the world stopped feeling good
[00:41.23]All the glitter lost its shine
[00:44.60]When Your truth collided with my life
[00:47.97]Now all I want is grace and faith
[00:51.35]A cross, not the crowns I tried to chase
[00:54.72]The world don’t pull me like it did
[00:58.09]My heart is Yours—I’m finally free
[01:01.46]I heard Your voice through the noise
[01:04.84]Calling me out of the mess I enjoyed
[01:08.21]Eyes opened wide, ears finally heard
[01:11.58]Every promise written inside Your Word
[01:14.96]What I lived for fell apart
[01:18.33]You rebuilt me, every piece of my heart
[01:21.70]What I thought I needed slipped through my hands
[01:25.08]But You gave me peace I don’t understand
[01:28.45]Yeah, You found me right where I stood
[01:31.82]When the world stopped feeling good
[01:35.20]All the idols lost their throne
[01:38.57]When You showed me I wasn’t alone
[01:41.94]Now I live for truth and light
[01:45.31]Not the crowd, not the fight
[01:48.69]The world don’t own me like it did
[01:52.06]My heart is Yours—I’m finally free
[01:55.43]No more chasing shadows
[01:58.81]No more living pretend
[02:02.18]I laid my old self down
[02:05.55]And was born again
[02:08.93]Salvation changed my name
[02:12.30]Faith rewrote my plans
[02:15.67]What the world couldn’t give
[02:19.04]You placed in my hands
[02:22.42]You found me right where I stood
[02:25.79]I'm no longer misunderstood
[02:29.16]Now eternity’s in my sight
[02:32.54]Not the world, not the night
[02:35.91]All I need is You alone
[02:39.28]Jesus, You’re my way back home
[02:42.66]The world lost its grip on me
[02:46.03]My heart is Yours—forever free
[02:49.40]I once lived for the world…
[02:52.78]Now I live for the Word.
[02:56.15]Yes, yes Jesus I live for you
